Print CBASS Summary

Prints a brief descripton of a fitted cbass object.

# S3 method for CBASS
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

a CBASS object returned by CARP
...

Unused additional generic arguements

Details

Reports number of observations and variables of dataset, any preprocessing done by the CBASS function, regularization weight information, the type of CBASS algorithm performed, and the visualizations returned.

Examples

library(clustRviz)
data("presidential_speech")
Xdat <- presidential_speech$X[1:10,1:4]
cbass.fit <- CBASS(
    X=Xdat)
#> Computing CBASS Path
#> Post-processing
print(cbass.fit)
#> CBASS Fit Summary
#> Number of Observations: 10
#> Number of Variables: 4
#> Pre-processing: global-center
#> Obs. Weights: RBF Kernel, phi = 0.025, k = 2
#> Var. Weights: RBF Kernel, phi = 0.01, k = 1
#> Algorithm: CBASS VIZ
#> Visualizations: Static DendStatic HeatmapInteractive Heatmap
#> Raw Data:
#>          [,1]     [,2]     [,3]     [,4]
#> [1,] 3.433987 2.397895 1.791759 2.564949
#> [2,] 4.248495 4.663439 2.995732 1.945910
#> [3,] 4.025352 3.091042 2.833213 3.332205
#> [4,] 1.386294 0.000000 0.000000 1.386294
#> [5,] 4.060443 4.174387 2.302585 4.304065
